===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|la}} {{term|moneta|monēta|place for making coins|lang=la}}, from the temple of [[w:Juno Moneta|Juno Moneta]] (named for {{term|Moneta|Monēta|lang=la}} mother of the Muses), where coins were made, akin to Danish {{term|mønte|lang=da}} (spelling before [[:w:de:Dänische Rechtschreibreform von 1948|the writing reform of 1948]]: {{term|mynte|lang=da}}), German {{term|münzen||to mint|lang=de}}, and to Russian {{term|монета|sc=Cyrl||coin|lang=ru}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A building or institution where money (originally, only [[coin]]s) is produced under government licence.
# {{context|informal}} A large amount of [[money]]. A [[vast]] [[sum]] or [[amount]], etc.
#: ''That house is worth a mint''
#: ''It must have cost a mint to produce!''

